         <abstract id="aspace_77208dc31c32d3a13fde3b88591e4c21">Letters and documents concerning Hill's activities as ambassador to the Hague and envoy to the Savoy. Also includes letters from James Bateman regarding financial matters and political appointments; from James Cressett regarding Cressett's work as a diplomat; from George Dolman regarding the naval maneuvers of the frigate, Lyme, of which Dolman was captain; and from Richard Powys regarding the passing of Hill's bills at the Treasury.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2009000254"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Hill, Richard, 1656?-1727</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
